Description: Rim sherd of fine-walled pottery kylix(?); near vertical and slightly concave; wholly glazed with three red lines on inside, one on outside; graffito inscription on outside.
Bibliographic references: Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 687, no. 449)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.375)
